---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base title="Resources">
  <article class="container page-section">
    <h1>Resources</h1>
    <p>Books, apps, websites, and practitioners to explore further.</p>

    <h2>Books</h2>
    <div class="card" style="margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">
      <strong>The Way Out</strong> — Alan Gordon and Alon Ziv. The definitive book on Pain Reprocessing Therapy. Practical, science-backed, and accessible.
    </div>
    <div class="card" style="margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">
      <strong>Unlearn Your Pain</strong> — Dr. Howard Schubiner. A workbook format with exercises for identifying and reversing neuroplastic pain.
    </div>
    <div class="card" style="margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">
      <strong>Explain Pain</strong> — David Butler and Lorimer Moseley. The classic text on pain science, used by clinicians worldwide.
    </div>
    <div class="card" style="margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">
      <strong>The Mindbody Prescription</strong> — Dr. John Sarno. The pioneering work that first described tension myoneural syndrome and brain-based pain.
    </div>

    <h2>Apps</h2>
    <div class="card" style="margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">
      <strong>Curable</strong> — Guided program combining pain science education, meditation, and somatic tracking. Evidence-informed.
    </div>
    <div class="card" style="margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">
      <strong>Waking Up</strong> — Meditation app with pain-focused content. Includes discussions with pain researchers and practitioners.
    </div>
    <div class="card" style="margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">
      <strong>Headspace</strong> — General mindfulness that helps with pain-related stress and sleep issues.
    </div>

    <h2>Websites</h2>
    <div class="card" style="margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">
      <strong><a href="https://www.lin.health" target="_blank">Lin Health</a></strong> — Online clinic specializing in neuroplastic pain. Has an excellent blog and treatment programs.
    </div>
    <div class="card" style="margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">
      <strong><a href="https://www.paintoolkit.org" target="_blank">Pain Toolkit</a></strong> — Free resource with practical strategies for managing chronic pain.
    </div>

    <h2>YouTube</h2>
    <div class="card" style="margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">
      <strong>Lorimer Moseley</strong> — Search for "Tame the Beast" and "Why Things Hurt." The best explainers on pain science.
    </div>
    <div class="card" style="margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">
      <strong>Howard Schubiner</strong> — Short animated videos explaining neuroplastic pain and how to treat it.
    </div>

    <h2>Practitioners</h2>
    <p>
      Look for clinicians trained in: Pain Reprocessing Therapy (PRT), Emotional Awareness and Expression 
      Therapy (EAET), or pain science-informed physical therapy. The <a href="https://www.lin.health" target="_blank">Lin Health</a> 
      directory and the <a href="https://www.psychologytoday.com" target="_blank">Psychology Today</a> 
      therapist finder (filter by chronic pain) are good starting points.
    </p>

    <div class="card" style="background: var(--teal-light); margin-top: 2rem;">
      <p style="margin: 0; font-size: 0.9rem;">
        <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> These are suggestions, not endorsements. Always research any 
        practitioner or program before committing. Results vary by individual.
      </p>
    </div>
  </article>
</Base>
